  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="KT330-kilavi">piriviṭai vēṟupaṭṭa kiḻatti tōḻikkuc colliyatu. </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">Uttered to the confidante by HER, who had changed in the
          time of separation. </p>
      </div>

      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="KT330">
          <l> nalattakaip pulaitti pacaitōyt teṭuttut</l>
          <l> talaippuṭaip pōkkit taṇkayat tiṭṭa</l>
          <l> nīriṟ piriyāp parūuttiri kaṭukkum</l>
          <l> pērilaip pakaṉṟaip potiyaviḻ vāṉpū</l>
          <l> viṉkaṭuṅ kaḷḷiṉ maṇamila kamaḻum</l>
          <l> puṉkaṇ mālaiyum pulampu</l>
          <l> miṉṟuko ṟōḻiyavar ceṉṟa nāṭṭē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg xml:lang="en">
          <l>In the land where he has gone,</l>
          <l rend="indent">where the bud-opening sky flowers of the big-leaved Pakaṉṟai</l>
          <l rend="indent">emit [their] smell <note place="foot"> <term xml:lang="ta"> maṇam ila kamaḻum </term> is literally "smelling without fragrance", that is presumably, emitting an unpleasant smell. </note>  like sweet, strong toddy,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">resembling the big twists [of cloth]: <note place="foot">Here we presumably have to understand an elliptical metaphor: <term xml:lang="ta"> tiri </term> means the piece of washed cloth wrung out by the washerwoman, as a comparison for the form of the Pakaṉṟai leaves. </note></l>
          <l rend="indent3">dipped in the paste [and] raised, beaten <note place="foot"> <term xml:lang="ta"> puṭai pōkki </term>: can the causative of <term xml:lang="ta"> pōku-tal </term> be explained as a kind of auxiliary here, expressing the force of the movement?     </note>  [on stones] with</l>
          <l rend="indent3">the end [and] put in the cool tank unseparated from the water,</l>
          <l rend="indent6">by the washerwoman fit for goodness, <note place="foot"> What can be the meaning of <term xml:lang="ta"> nalam takai </term>? T.V.G.'s explanation is something like "fit for work", which remains rather pale.   </note> </l>
          <l>aren't there, friend, sorrowful evenings and loneliness?</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
